This package provides a set of modules to manage a DPM site using Puppet.

WHAT IS PUPPET

  Puppet has been developed to help the sysadmin community move to building 
  and sharing mature tools that avoid the duplication of everyone solving 
  the same problem.

  You can find a lot more details at its website:
  http://www.puppetlabs.com/

WHAT IS DPM

  DPM is the Disk Pool Manager, developed within the LHC Computing Grid (LCG) 
  project. It provides a lightweight solution for disk storage manager, 
  supporting commonly used grid protocols such as SRM, GRIDFTP, RFIO, ...

  You can find a lot more details about this software on its website:
  https://svnweb.cern.ch/trac/lcgdm/wiki/Dpm

DOCUMENTATION

  In the 'manifests' directory you can find one file with the configuration of
  each of our different testbed sites at CERN IT/GT/DMS.

  These manifests rely on a set of modules. For instructions on how to setup
  these modules, check https://svnweb.cern.ch/trac/lcgdm/wiki/Dpm/Admin/Puppet.

REQUIREMENTS

  Current manifests require puppet 0.25 or above.
